Hagman interpreted the role of Ewing as a corrupt, insatiable man with a charismatic smile: an insidious businessman and infidel husband who sought to have his alcoholic wife Sue Ellen (Linda Gray) expelled.
"I know what should be on the tombstone of J.R.," Hagman said in 1988.
It should be called "Here rests the honourable citizen J.R. Ewing".
This is the only business he didn't win.
